{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"After looking at your code, i'm afraid to say that you are not using `AnimationMixer` correctly. If you call `mixer.clipAction( 'rotate' )`, the root object of the mixer needs the animations attached to its geometry or to itself. This is not the case in your application. You should do something like this:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nconst object = gltf.scene;\r\nobject.animations = gltf.animations;\r\n\r\nmixer = new THREE.AnimationMixer( object );\r\n\r\nobject.animations.forEach( animation => {\r\n\r\n   mixer.clipAction( animation ).play();\r\n\r\n} );\r\n```\r\nYour subsequent calls of `clipAction()` will work then. Besides, I can see multiple problems in your scene:\r\n\r\n- You are not adding the loaded `glTF` object to the scene\r\n- Use `WebGLRenderer` instead of `CanvasRenderer`\r\n\r\nPlease visit the [forum](https:\/\/discourse.threejs.org\/) if you need more help.","created_at":"2018-01-24T14:47:54.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13167#issuecomment-360158115","id":360158115,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13167","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2MDE1ODExNQ==","updated_at":"2018-01-24T15:42:53.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/360158115","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"h